column29: Protocols: Samples were quickly collected from the petri dishes with fine tweezers, dried with tissue paper, placed into an eppendorf tube and immediately snap frozen. Plants were grown in vitro for two weeks on petri dishes containing MS media with 2% sucrose. Plants were grown under long day conditions with approx. 100 micromol photons per second per square meter Plants were sprayed with water using a standard hairspray bottle (mister) RNA was prepared using the Sigma Plant Spectrum Total kit, with on-column DNA digestion and Ambion DNA-free kit Libraries were constructed using the Illumina RiboZero Plant kit
